			<body><div id="63--on-the-slain-at-chickamauga">

				<pb facs="/images/battle-pieces-v1/battle-pieces-i-0180.jpg"/>
				<head type="main">
				<hi rend="italic">On the Slain at Chickamauga.</hi>
				</head>
				<head type="sub-head"><hi rend="italic"></hi>
				</head>
<lg>
<l><hi rend="smallcaps">Happy</hi> are they and charmed in life</l>
<l rend="2em">Who through long wars arrive unscarred</l>
<l>At peace. To such the wreath be given,</l>
<l>If they unfalteringly have striven—</l>
<l n="5" rend="2em">In honor, as in limb, unmarred.</l>
<l>Let cheerful praise be rife,</l>
<l rend="2em">And let them live their years at ease,</l>
<l>Musing on brothers who victorious died—</l>
<l rend="2em">Loved mates whose memory shall ever please.</l>
</lg>
<lg>
<l n="10">And yet mischance is honorable too—</l>
<l rend="2em">Seeming defeat in conflict justified</l>
<l>Whose end to closing eyes is hid from view.</l>
<l>The will, that never can relent—</l>
<l>The aim, survivor of the bafflement,</l>
<l n="15" rend="4em">Make this memorial due.</l>
</lg>
</div></body>
